<h5 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h5>
<p>Compute <span class="process-math">\(v\text{.}\)</span> This will be the terminal velocity of the sand settling in the water. Notice that this should be independent of <span class="process-math">\(v_0\text{.}\)</span> How does your answer for terminal velocity depend on <span class="process-math">\(M=m-m_w\)</span> and <span class="process-math">\(R\text{?}\)</span> Does this make sense physically?</p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#p-54" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
